ualified class name in the superclass documentation link, so that's a minor hints_missing issue. The intro does provide context about when to use this handler—specifically for special transitions like forcing a login redirect when unauthenticated. While the code examples demonstrate the use case and the sections cover configuration details, this explicit \"when to use\" guidance isn't captured elsewhere in the documentation. I'll keep this as a finding since it helps users understand when this handler is appropriate compared to alternatives.\n\nFor the second finding, the fully qualified name `nablarch.fw.handler.RewriteRule` is missing from section 4, which would be valuable for users searching for implementation details. I'll report this as a minor hints_missing issue.\n\nLet me do a final check to make sure I haven't overlooked anything else in the documentation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16908,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16908,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9daa1945-9367-4971-8c10-fffe3206a190","uuid":"84e1a49d-0c58-4cca-a94f-aff85a1a824f"}
